    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as an interactive dashboard rather than a linear report. It starts with a compelling Hero section with key value propositions. The core of the app is the "One-Stop 지원 프로그램" section, featuring 5 interactive cards for each support module. Clicking a card dynamically displays its detailed content, preventing information overload. This is followed by a visual, clickable timeline for the "추진 일정" and a "기대 효과" section with icons for scannability. A donut chart visualizes the "재원 확보 방안". A new "AI 인허가 가능성 진단" section is added, allowing users to input device details and receive an AI-generated assessment of approval likelihood and key considerations. This task-oriented structure allows potential applicants (SMEs, startups) to quickly understand the program's value and explore the specific services relevant to them, enhancing usability over a static document. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Report Info: 5 Support Modules (A-E) -> Goal: Organize & Inform -> Viz/Method: Interactive Grid of 5 Cards -> Interaction: Click to show/hide details -> Justification: Breaks down complex services into manageable chunks, user controls information flow. | Report Info: 추진 일정 -> Goal: Show Process/Change -> Viz/Method: Horizontal HTML/CSS Timeline -> Interaction: Click to highlight and display stage details -> Justification: More engaging than a static list, visualizes program flow. | Report Info: 재원 확보 방안 -> Goal: Compare Proportions -> Viz/Method: Chart.js Donut Chart -> Interaction: Hover for tooltips -> Justification: Quickly communicates the composition of funding sources. | Report Info: 기대 효과 -> Goal: Inform -> Viz/Method: Icon Grid -> Interaction: Static icons with text -> Justification: Enhances scannability and memorability of key benefits. | Report Info: Medical Device Approval Likelihood -> Goal: Assess & Inform -> Viz/Method: AI-powered text generation -> Interaction: User input, button click to generate assessment -> Justification: Provides a novel, interactive tool for users to get preliminary insights into their device's approval potential. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
